The '''silent service code''' is a way for a diner to "talk" to [[Waiting staff|servers]] during a meal without saying a word, mainly to tell them that the diner is finished.  This will prevent any embarrassing situations where the server would take a meal prematurely.

To tell a server you have finished place your [[napkin]] to the left of your [[Plate (dishware)|plate]], and place all your [[food utensil|utensils]] together in a "4-o'clock" position on your plate.

Utensils crossed on a plate signify that a diner is still eating.

If you must leave during the meal, you should place the napkin on your chair to avoid any confusion.

The code is almost always taught during business dining [[etiquette]] classes.

